While loops allows us to repeat code multiple times. 

The first basic loop is the while loop, which will continually execute a block of code while a condition remains True

x = 1 
while x <= 3:
  print(x)
  
  #Keep adding 1 to x variable
  x = x + 1
  
  >> 1
  >> 2
  >> 3
  
  
  Salir de un bucle infinito: 
  
  Kernel en Anaconda 
  
  Ctr + C en Python IDE 
  
  Para salir de bucles infinitos con True usando break. 
